---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SiteHeader from "../../components/SiteHeader.astro";
import Card from "../../components/Card.astro";
import LinkButton from "../../components/LinkButton.astro";
import { withBase } from '../../utils/paths';
import { buildSEO } from '../../utils/seo';

const seo = buildSEO({
  title: "Origin - How ArcUp Began",
  description: "The story of how a question about open science and a small experiment with plasma became ArcUp — a framework for regenerative research.",
  path: "/about/origin",
  siteUrl: Astro.site,
});
---

<BaseLayout {...seo}>
  <SiteHeader active="about" />
  
  <main id="main-content" class="page-shell page-origin">
    
    <!-- Breadcrumb -->
    <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href={withBase("/about")}>About</a>
      <span aria-hidden="true">/</span>
      <span aria-current="page">Origin</span>
    </nav>

    <!-- Hero -->
    <header class="origin-hero">
      <h1>How ArcUp Began</h1>
    </header>

    <!-- The Question -->
    <section class="origin-section">
      <h2 aria-label="Introduction: The question that inspired ArcUp">A Question That Started It All</h2>
      <p class="origin-question">
        What if the next big breakthrough was built in the open?
      </p>
      <p>
        That question stayed with me. It wasn't about a specific device or formula — it was about what kind of future 
        we might create if <em>discovery itself became a shared act</em>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Arc^ began not as a product, but as a moment of reflection on how science could return to care, transparency, 
        and collaboration.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Early Experiments -->
    <Card as="section" class="experiments-section">
      <h2 aria-label="ArcUp early experiments with plasma and seed germination">Early Experiments — The First Spark</h2>
      <div class="experiments-content">
        <p>
          ArcUp began in a small room with a flyback transformer, a driver circuit, and a few glass electrodes. 
          I had been reading plasma research papers from around the world — seeing how different teams were exploring 
          plasma-water interactions — and decided to test it for myself.
        </p>
        <p>
          My goal was simple: to see whether plasma could influence seed germination.
        </p>
        <p class="experiments-highlight">
          And it did.
        </p>
        <p>
          That small moment — watching seeds respond — revealed a larger truth: plasma can alter biological processes, 
          and the tools to study it don't have to belong to large institutions.
        </p>
        <p>
          It also raised new questions: If I can do this alone, what would it look like if <em>we did it together</em> — in the open?
        </p>
      </div>
    </Card>

    <!-- The Pattern -->
    <section class="pattern-section">
      <h2 aria-label="The systemic issues ArcUp responds to">The Pattern We Refuse</h2>
      <p>
        Looking back across centuries, I saw a cycle repeating:
      </p>
      
      <div class="pattern-cycle">
        <div class="cycle-item">Conflict</div>
        <div class="cycle-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="cycle-item">Production</div>
        <div class="cycle-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="cycle-item">Patents</div>
        <div class="cycle-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="cycle-item">Profit</div>
        <div class="cycle-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="cycle-item">Power</div>
        <div class="cycle-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="cycle-item">Harm</div>
      </div>

      <p class="pattern-description">
        A pattern of extraction dressed up as progress.
      </p>

      <Card class="pattern-today">
        <h3>Today it looks like this:</h3>
        <ul class="pattern-list">
          <li>Curiosity gated by funding</li>
          <li>Discovery delayed for the market</li>
          <li>Scale replacing meaning</li>
          <li>Science run as strategy, not as a humble search for knowledge</li>
        </ul>
      </Card>

      <div class="pattern-response">
        <p>
          ArcUp was born from a refusal of that pattern. It's not rebellion for its own sake — it's a reorientation.
        </p>
        <p class="pattern-emphasis">
          A way of saying that knowledge should circulate, not accumulate. That progress should heal, not harm.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Framework -->
    <Card as="section" class="framework-origin-section">
      <h2 aria-label="Transition from individual experiment to open framework">A Framework, Not a Lab</h2>
      <p>
        ArcUp grew from this reflection into a framework — a set of methods, values, and open tools for regenerative 
        plasma research. It integrates my background in ecology, computer science, and systems thinking, but sits 
        outside the usual institutions that govern innovation.
      </p>
      <p>
        It's science re-practised — built to serve <em>life</em>, not ownership.
      </p>
      <div class="framework-closing">
        <p>
          Arc^ began as one person's experiment.
        </p>
        <p class="closing-emphasis">
          It continues as a collective invitation: to research, to repair, to remember what science can be.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Card>

    <!-- Navigation -->
    <nav class="origin-nav" aria-label="Continue exploring">
      <LinkButton 
        href={withBase("/about/founder")} 
        variant="primary"
        icon="arrow-right"
      >
        Meet the Founder
      </LinkButton>
      <LinkButton 
        href={withBase("/about/mission")} 
        variant="outline"
        icon="arrow-right"
      >
        Explore the Mission
      </LinkButton>
    </nav>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-origin {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--section-gap);
    max-width: 85ch;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* Breadcrumb */
  .breadcrumb {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: var(--color-primary-bright);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color var(--transition-base);
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover,
  .breadcrumb a:focus-visible {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  /* Hero */
  .origin-hero {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .origin-hero h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: var(--text-4xl);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  /* Origin Section */
  .origin-section {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .origin-section h2 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .origin-question {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
    color: var(--color-primary-bright);
    font-style: italic;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: rgba(10, 147, 150, 0.08);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-primary-bright);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    margin: 1rem 0 2rem 0;
  }

  .origin-section p {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  /* Experiments Section */
  .experiments-section {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .experiments-section h2 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .experiments-content {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .experiments-content p {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .experiments-highlight {
    font-size: var(--text-xl) !important;
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold) !important;
    color: var(--color-text) !important;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1rem 0;
  }

  /* Pattern Section */
  .pattern-section {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .pattern-section h2 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .pattern-section > p {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .pattern-cycle {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
    padding: 2rem 1rem;
    background: rgba(6, 12, 22, 0.4);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  }

  .cycle-item {
    padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    background: rgba(10, 147, 150, 0.12);
    border: 1px solid rgba(93, 225, 228, 0.3);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
  }

  .cycle-arrow {
    color: var(--color-primary-bright);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
  }

  .pattern-description {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: var(--text-lg) !important;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text) !important;
  }

  .pattern-today {
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .pattern-today h3 {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .pattern-list {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .pattern-list li {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .pattern-list li::before {
    content: "×";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-primary-bright);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
  }

  .pattern-response {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .pattern-response p {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .pattern-emphasis {
    font-size: var(--text-lg) !important;
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium) !important;
    color: var(--color-text) !important;
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  /* Framework Origin Section */
  .framework-origin-section {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .framework-origin-section h2 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .framework-origin-section > p {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .framework-closing {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .framework-closing p {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .closing-emphasis {
    font-size: var(--text-xl) !important;
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium) !important;
    color: var(--color-text) !important;
  }

  /* Navigation */
  .origin-nav {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .origin-hero h1 {
      font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    }

    .pattern-cycle {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: stretch;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .cycle-arrow {
      transform: rotate(90deg);
    }

    .origin-nav {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
  }
</style>